  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there was no problem to go from one part of the country into the other, so that was no problem to go and establish yourself in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The Hungarians were welcoming all sorts of people at that time, because Hungary was under the Turkish rule for about 150 years, and most of the population has disappeared.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So actually, the middle part of Hungary-- the flatland-- was uninhabited, and there were all sorts of people-- mostly [INAUDIBLE], the Germans, and Slovaks from Slovakia, who were established in Hungary, where they were living in certain villages.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the villages were speaking only-- the people in the villages-- were speaking only German.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Or in the other village, they were speaking only Slovaks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they weren't learning to speak Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "On the other hand, when the Jews came to Hungary, they were willing to learn Hun-- Hungarian, and they were very successful.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "During the second half of the 19th century, they were mostly businessmen, and doctors, and lawyers, and they were poets and authors and they were writing in the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they were very, very successful-- more not [INAUDIBLE] came during or after the second World War, to Hollywood, were producing many successful movies-- like one of them is and many others afterward.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now eventually, during the-- after the first World War, between the two World Wars, the Hungarians realized that the Jews are taking over the [? literary ?] life of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And they just didn't like it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the Jews were oppressed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "First they had the numerous clauses, which meant about 3% of the Jews could enter university.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then later on, after '38, there was a [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which meant that no Jew could enter the university.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
